Dr. Drechsler. â\\x80\\x9cEven if bureaucrats think like ordinary citizens, they still need to be able to look at the types of techno-economic development, and that is a huge challenge.â\\x80\\x9d', 'Over the past decade, Mohammed Abdulateef has amassed an impressive array of football memorabilia â\\x80\\x93 and with just weeks to go until the next edition of the tournament in Qatar, he is sharing his collection of FIFA World Cupâ\\x84¢ mascots with people in Doha. Organised by the Supreme Committee for Delivery & Legacy (SC), the exhibition features every FIFA World Cupâ\\x84¢ mascot since 1966. The display is located on the first floor of City Center Mall and is open daily from 8 AM to 10 PM until 20 December.We spoke to Abdulateef, who also holds one of the most valuable and complete collection of FIFA World Cupâ\\x84¢ tickets, to learn more about his passion, and also his aspirations for this yearâ\\x80\\x99s tournament, which will get underway on 20 November when Qatar face Ecuador at Al Bayt Stadium. ', 'With only weeks to go until Qatar hosts the first FIFA World Cupâ\\x84¢ in the Middle East and Arab world, the Supreme Committee for Delivery & Legacy (SC), in close collaboration with FIFA, is wrapping up preparations for the tournament and the legacy it will deliver.In this new series, Making History, we are focusing on the work of Qatari employees who have played a key role in the SCâ\\x80\\x99s journey. This week, we speak to Faisal Khalid, Ambassador Programme Manager. Faisal, from Al Rayyan, joined the SC in October 2019 after studying abroad and obtaining a degree in accounting. What do you remember about the day Qatar won the bid to host the FIFA World Cupâ\\x84¢?I think every Qatari who witnessed Qatar winning the bid will cherish this memory forever. I remember I was away on a trip with friends and we were watching the TV in a coffee shop. The crowd suddenly cheered and we celebrated on the streets. There are no words to describe my feelings on that 