 include projects across the Middle East and North Africa (MENA) in 2012. It is the regionâ\\x80\\x99s first integrated and performance-based system that assesses and rates buildings and infrastructure for their sustainability impacts. GSAS is aimed at improving the design, construction and operations of buildings while also identifying sustainability challenges specific to the MENA regionâ\\x80\\x99s building environment. In 2014, FIFA approved GSAS as the sustainability rating system to assess all infrastructure built for this yearâ\\x80\\x99s World Cup.â\\x80\\x9cFrom the very beginning, sustainability has been at the heart of all of our projects for Qatar 2022,â\\x80\\x9d said Eng. Bodour Al Meer, the SCâ\\x80\\x99s Sustainability Executive Director. â\\x80\\x9cWe are thankful to GORD for helping us to reach our sustainability targets by auditing each of our World Cup stadium sites 11 times. The projects we have delivered showcase the impact of hosting the first FIFA World Cup in the region and are helping to push the sustainability message further than ever before.â\\x80\\x9d ', 'Some of Asiaâ\\x80\\x99s biggest stars will perform at the Bollywood Music Festival â\\x80\\x93 which will be held at Lusail Stadium in Qatar on Friday 4 November.Some of Asiaâ\\x80\\x99s biggest stars will perform at the Bollywood Music Festival â\\x80\\x93 which will be held at Lusail Stadium in Qatar on Friday 4 November.Superstar singer Rahat Fateh Ali Khan is confirmed on the bill, along with singer Sunidhi Chauhan and composing duo Salim-Sulaiman. Rahat is a Pakistani performer and a popular playback singer in Hindi cinema. Chauhan is an award-winning singer and TV talent show judge from India. Salim-Sulaiman is a score composing duo consisting of brothers Salim and Sulaiman Merchant.Superstar singer Rahat Fateh Ali Khan is confirmed on the bill, along with singer Sunidhi Chauhan and composing duo Salim-Sulaiman. Rahat is a Pakistani performer and a popular playback singer in Hin